@node AmigaGuideALS "ALS for AmigaGuide - Instructions"
@{i}By Chris Young 1997@{ui}

Come on, this is getting ridiculous.  The original ALS - fine.  Enhanced ALS - yeah, just a better version of the original.  ALS Professional - would be good if it ever got completed.  WB-ALS - A logical step to make ALS multitask.  Emulator Versions - A demonstration of what can be achieved on different platforms.  ALS.library - lets other people implement ALS into their programs.  But a version for INSTALLER????  ALS running on a program designed to INSTALL SOFTWARE? It isn't even very good (ALS, not Installer).  Then there's this... ALS for AmigaGuide.  AMIGAGUIDE - A Hypertext document displayer, with absolutely no graphics facilities, and links ALWAYS go to the same place - so no random messages.  It can't be done, and people are getting fed up with so many different similar versions of ALS anyway, so why bother?  I don't know.  I just created it to make yet another obscure Amiga version of ALS.

Requires Spectrum.font!

This is a version of ALS for AmigaGuide.  Just click on 'START' below...
To mow, you must use @{b}Browse >@{ub} (you can even 'un-mow')

Have Fun.
@{jcenter}@{"START" link AGALS}
@endnode

