@node ALSlib-libALS "LibraryALS - ALS using ALS.library"
This is a complete version of ALS, using the Als() routine in als.library

Now you can specify a prefs file to use if you start it from the command line. (als.library 4.1 and newer only)

TEMPLATE: LibraryALS [config file|SCREEN]

If no config file is specified, the default ENV:ALS/Library.prefs will be used instead.

@{b}Warning@{ub}: Neither als.library nor LibraryALS check whether files exist or are valid config files.  Strange things may/will happen if you specify non-config or non-existant files.

If SCREEN is specified (als.library 6 required), then LibraryALS will open a screen and run ALS on that instead.
Please Note: If SCREEN is specified, then you cannot also specify a seperate config file

*** als.library 6.0 ***

Instead of using 'SCREEN', you can create an environment variable;

SetEnv ENV:ALS/Screen 1

This has exactly the same effect as typing SCREEN on the command line. (except you @{i}can@{ui} now specify a config file to use)

Note that setting the environmental variable "SCREEN" will affect ALL usage of als.library, not just LibraryALS.

*** als.library 6.1/ALSPrefs 1.4 ***

There is a toggle switch in ALSPrefs that performs the above function.
@endnode

