@node FlexALS "The Flex (emulator) Version..."
The file FlexALS is a Flex virtual disk for use with Ben Williams' FLEX Emulation System.  It should be placed in the same directory as FLEX.

To get it running, you need to issue the following commands:

@{b}LOGIN FlexALS 1@{ub} - This will put the virtual disk into virtual drive 1
                     The previous disk will be logged out automatically, and
                     any changes will be saved to the virtual disk file.
@{b}BASIC FlexALS@{ub}   - Loads and runs ALS

@{u}Notes on this version@{uu}

Flex BASIC is a bit rubbish (it is very similar to C64 BASIC), and lacks a few commands which are needed for ALS.  Therefore, there are no graphics (not even stars), and you have to press Return after 'M' to mow.  It is also about fifty thousand times slower than it should be (run FLEX on an '060!).
Another problem is memory: Somehow, an Amiga ASCII file of 3K manages to use up all 30K-ish of FLEX BASIC.  I had to split the game into two sections and use 'virtual arrays'.  These seem to have a small character limit, and the result is that the messages at the end of the game only include about two words.  The scroll routine doesn't work properly either, but there's no point in fixing it because of the character limit problem.
Please note that after the end message, it is Q that scrolls and any other key to go back to the menu - not the other way round, as stated.
@endnode

