@node WBALS "Advanced Lawnmower Simulator for Workbench"
@{u}WB-ALS (for Workbench)@{uu}

These are the same as the standard or enhanced versions of ALS, but run in a Workbench window.

WB-ALS requires hisoftbasic.library (unfortunately.  I tried to get it to work in ACE BASIC, but all the text formatting went wrong), and has the following extra features (in pull-down menus):

1. Window...

This allows you to configure the window size.  Due to HiSoft BASIC V1 being ancient (1989), you are limited to a maximum window size of 640×512.  This means there is no point in increasing the workbench screen size or resolution beyond this (eg. Super-Hires Laced) specially to play a massive game of ALS.

If you press 'c' on this window, you can configure the shape of the sun.  Ideally, this should be circular.  (I actually only put this in for my use, but you may as well know about it)

2. Use Screen

This opens a custom Low-res screen for ALS.

3. Sound

This is a toggle item which allows you to turn the sound on or off.

4. Spectrum

This is another toggle item, which should be set to whether or not you have the Spectrum.font installed in fonts:.  In fact, the default is on and if it doesn't find the font it doesn't crash or go wrong or anything, you'll just get wierd characters for the graphics. (NOTE: The font must be in MEMORY.  You can initialise it by using the included application "InitSpeccyFont".  Put it in user-startup, or something.  Or double-click on it when you want to run WB-ALS.)  If you turn it off, ALS will default to using topaz/8 and some make-shift "graphics" like the ones found in the @{"RM380Z" link RM380Z} version.
(This really ought to be on auto-detection, but I've lost the source code...)
5. Load Config

Loads previously saved preferences.  This is done automatically when you start WB-ALS.  If it refuses to load, then the window size in the config file is set too large.  Change the screen mode or delete WB-ALS.config (in the program's directory).

6. Save Config

Saves your current preferences (window size, sun shape, sound, screen, font, colour assignments).

7. About...

Shows some information about WB-ALS

8. Quit

Does the same as the close gadget in the top left of the window border.

9. ALS+ included features (not a menu item)

These include the turbo mode and secret hidden mower.

10. Colours menu

     a) ALS Palette
     
     This changes some the colours in positions 9-11 of the Workbench palette, so the colours ALS uses look right.  It is better, however, to use/save some colour assignments which are correct for your WB palette (see below).  This is because changing the palette has to be done manually every time you start ALS (may be annoying) and also it may, possibly, affect Magic WB icons if you are using Workbench 3 with an 16-colour palette.  It might also affect WB2 or 3 8-colour screens, but I doubt it.
     
     Now for a quick moan about MagicWB icons: Why do some people like to force the first eight colours on a WB3 machine, just so those MWB icons @{i}all @{ui}look pretty?  WHAT IS THE POINT?  I mean, you can quite easily switch to 8-colour mode (so IconEdit works properly), load all the "faulty" icons into it, select edit -> copy from the pull-downs, select edit -> paste and then do the same with the second image (if it has one), and save them out again.  IS IT @{I}REALLY @{UI}@{U}THAT@{UU} HARD?  Now, if only we went back to WB3-style MagicWB icons, using colours n-4 etc...

     b) Assign...
     
     This brings up a little window with some colours and words on it.  If you click on a block, the colour which is used to depict the colour it's supposed to be depicting can be changed (eh?).  For example, because you probably didn't understand that, if you click on:
     
     @{bg highlight}WHITE @{bg background}
     
     This will change to
     
     @{bg fill}WHITE @{BG BACKGROUND}
     
     and next time ALS requests white, it will get blue instead.
     
     @{b}Use Default@{ub} will change all the assignments back to the defaults.
     
     @{b}Use MagicWB@{ub} will change the assignments to use the MagicWB colours only (ie. ALS will become mostly greyscale).  This uses colours n-4, n-3 etc. NOT colours 4-8.  So you have no excuse to keep forcing MWB Colours into those positions (rant, rave).

11. @{"Last minute important notes" link WB-ALS.readme}

	Click on the button, then.
