@node WB-ALS.readme
IMPORTANT LAST-MINUTE WB-ALS NOTES
==================================

1. When using a screen font larger than 8 pt, WB-ALS doesn't work quite as well.  (ie. the stuff in the window scrolls on the bottom line of grass)

2. The Spectrum font isn't always being used when it should be.
» It must be in @{b}MEMORY@{ub}.  To achieve this, you must run one of the standard ALS's first, and quit with Ctrl-C, or run @{"InitSpeccyFont" link InitFont}.  Then run WB-ALS and it'll work.

3. I've lost the source code (I think I used the disk for something else), and although I'm pretty sure I've got a back-up, I have yet to find it.  Basically, that means I can't fix these bugs.
@endnode

@node InitFont "InitSpeccyFont"
@{u}InitSpeccyFont@{uu}

This little utility loads the Spectrum.font font into memory, so it can be used by @{"WB-ALS" link WBALS}.
Just double-click it before starting WB-ALS, or put it in your user-startup/WBStartUp.
@endnode

